-----------------------------------------------------------------

                       Smtlink README

-----------------------------------------------------------------

Smtlink is a trusted clause processor that provides an interface
for integrating an external SMT solver into ACL2.

The default SMT solver integrated is Z3.

-----------------------------------------------------------------

                     REQUIREMENTS

1. Z3 is properly installed. It should be included in the system
   PATH.
2. ACL2 is properly installed. It should be included in the
   system PATH.
3. Smtlink uses Unix commands that requires Unix environment.

----------------------------------------------------------------

                  BUILD INSTRUCTIONS

1. Follow :doc cert.pl to certify the books using command
   "cert.pl top.lisp".
2. To setup environment for Python, add
   export PYTHONPATH=*Smtlink-directory*/z3_interface
   into your .bashrc file.

----------------------------------------------------------------

                     USAGE

Refer to document "Extending ACL2 with SMT techniques"
for usage.
